    "faq_with_image_m73Xra": {
      "type": "faq-with-image",
      "blocks": {
        "accordion_GhRGXt": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "accordion_header": "How can I ensure a commissioned bracelet is perfectly sized for my unique wrist shape?",
            "open_by_default": false,
            "text": "<p>A perfect fit transforms a lovely piece into an immediate heirloom. The process of commissioning bespoke bracelets requires meticulous attention to scale and measurement. </p><p>Our master goldsmiths are adept at designing pieces that drape beautifully, whether you prefer the solid structure of a bangle or the delicate articulation of a chain bracelet. </p><p>We strongly recommend arranging a private consultation at our Chichester Showroom; this guided assessment allows us to take precise measurements in person, ensuring your final creation is flawlessly proportioned for you near{{ block.settings.page.metafields.custom.location.value }}.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_HmVJLJ": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "accordion_header": "How do I ensure that all materials used in my bracelet (metals and stones) maintain ethical standards?",
            "open_by_default": false,
            "text": "<p>Maintaining the integrity of the material story is paramount. Whether we are working with 100% recycled Platinum, Kimberley Process-certified natural diamonds, or our responsible lab-grown alternatives, every component undergoes rigorous ethical verification. </p><p>Our commitment to ethically sourced materials applies from the initial sketch stage through to the final hand-finishing in our workshop. </p><p>For complete assurance and a detailed review of material provenance—whether you are commissioning from {{ block.settings.page.metafields.custom.location.value }} or far beyond—we recommend an appointment at the Chichester Showroom.<br/><br/></p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_xFhTbU": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "accordion_header": "Do you handle the remodelling of family bangles or wrist cuffs inherited from previous generations?",
            "open_by_default": false,
            "text": "<p>We treat every vintage piece with profound respect and unparalleled skill. Whether adapting a delicate Victorian bangle or restoring a heavy family cuff, our artisans focus on preserving the original legacy while modernising its wearability. This meticulous restoration work takes place entirely within the secure confines of our on-site Chichester workshop—your jewellery never leaves our protection. We welcome you to book an appointment at the Showroom so we can assess your beloved items from {{ block.settings.page.metafields.custom.location.value }}.<br/><br/></p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_pxHnfz": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "accordion_header": "What is the difference between a chain bracelet and a solid bangle and which suits my lifestyle?",
            "open_by_default": false,
            "text": "<p>The choice hinges upon desired impact and comfort. A solid bangle offers an air of timeless, structural strength, while a hand-crafted chain bracelet allows for fluid movement and incorporates versatile design elements (like individual charms or link formations). </p><p>We advise considering your daily routine—from the formality of Greater London to a relaxed day in Surrey—to determine the optimal style balance. Our private consultation at the Showroom will allow us to view these contrastive pieces side-by-side, helping you discover your perfect wrist statement while respecting your specific needs in {{ block.settings.page.metafields.custom.location.value }}.<br/><br/></p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_BRezAN": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "accordion_header": "Do I need an appointment to view wristwear?",
            "open_by_default": false,
            "text": "<p>You are welcome to browse our collection at any time. However, for bespoke commissions or to view specific high-value pieces, we recommend booking an appointment for a home visit so we can have everything ready for you.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "accordion_GhRGXt",
        "accordion_HmVJLJ",
